<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 20 Killed, 22 Injured in Freak Accident in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Twenty people were crushed to
death and 22 others injured when a tree uprooted by strong winds
fell on a Himachal Road Transport Corporation bus in Kinnaur
district of Himachal Pradesh in east India, local police said.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen people, including the driver and conductor of the bus,
died at the scene.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Trust of India, the ill-fated bus, which
was on its way from Sangala to Sarkaghat, was carrying some 50
passengers when the accident took place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
