<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Calls for Complete Nuclear Disarmament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia wants all nuclear
weapon states (NWS) to manifest their political will towards
achieving complete nuclear disarmament, Malaysia's national news
agency Bernama reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"With the desired political will and a creative approach, the
end goal is attainable," the news agency quoted Malaysia's
Permanent Representative to the United Nations Hasmy Agam as
saying at the 2000 Review Conference of the State Parties to the
Treaty On The Non-Proliferation Of Nuclear Weapons at the U.N. in
New York on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the goodwill and patience of the non-nuclear weapon
states are under severe strain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
