<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Manufacturing Sector Grows 6.8 Pct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The year-on-year volume of
production in the Philippine manufacturing sector rose 6.8 percent
in February, the National Statistics Office said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Based on its monthly survey of selected industries, the office
said average capacity utilization for February was 81.2 percent,
virtually unchanged from 81.1 percent previously.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the office said petroleum refineries and electrical
machinery posted the biggest growth in terms of value and volume
of production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
