<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India, Russia to Hold Security Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 26 (Xinhua) -- India and Russia will hold
talks on security-related issues during the visit of Russian
Secretary of National Security Council Sergei Ivanov, who is due
to arrive here later Wednesday evening, sources with the Indian
External Affairs Ministry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov, who is heading a high-level Russian delegation, will
hold talks with his counterpart Indian National Security Advisor
Brajesh Mishra and also sign a protocol with the Indian side, the
sources added.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day stay, Ivanov will also call on Indian
Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee, External Affairs Minister
Jaswant Singh and Defense Minister George Fernandes, they said.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov's visit is also believed to be paving the way for a
possible visit to India by Russian President-elect Vladimir Putin,
the final date of which is yet to be fixed, sources here said.
</P>
<P>
Russia and India agreed at the end of 1998 to move towards a
strategic partnership, while a declaration on such partnership is
expected to be signed during the next summit of leaders of both
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Trust of India, a total of 60 agreements
have been concluded between India and Russia since 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
