<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FPDA to Conduct Joint Marine/Air-Defense Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore Ministry of
Defense said Wednesday that the Five Power Defense Arrangements (
FPDA) will conduct a combined and joint Maritime and Air Defense
Exercise (ADEX) from April 27 to May 4, refraining from exactly
designating the exercise venue.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, code-named ADEX 2000, is to exercise the forces
of FPDA, which groups Australia, Malaysia, New Zealand, Singapore
and Britain, in protecting the integrity of the Malaysian and
Singapore air space and to enhance inter-operability, the ministry
said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The FPDA, a regional security framework designed "to contribute
to a more predictable and constructive pattern of relations in the
region," holds exercises regularly in the region annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
