<HEADLINE> New Zealand PM to Visit Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 26 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand Prime Minister
Helen Clark will pay a working visit to Singapore from April 27 to
28, the Singapore Ministry of Foreign Affairs said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It said that during her visit, Clark will call on Singapore
President S. R. Nathan, Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong and Senior
Minister Lee Kuan Yew.
</P>
<P>
She will also meet with Singapore Deputy Prime Minister Lee
Hsien Loong and visit the Singapore Science Park.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first visit by Clark after she took the
premiership last year.
</P>
<P>
Singapore enjoys close and warm ties with New Zealand and the
two countries have maintained frequent high-level exchanges.
</P>
</TEXT>
