<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jeep Mishap Kills Seven in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and
five others seriously injured Wednesday when an overloaded jeep
plunged into a valley in Palba district, western Nepal, Radio
Nepal reported.
</P>
<P>
The jeep fell 400 meters down into the valley at the turn of a
narrow mountain road, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
It quoted a witness as saying that the jeep was driving so fast
that it could not make a proper turn.
</P>
<P>
But the radio quoted a police source as saying the cause of the
accident was still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
