<HEADLINE> Leaving Imperial Park Understandable: Kentucky Fried Chicken (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
But, Liu said, the decision will not affect his appetite for
Kentucky Fried Chicken food. He said he will continue to take his
family, especially his son, to other KFC fast food restaurants in
other parts of the capital.
</P>
<P>
There are now 380 Kentucky Fried Chicken restaurants in 90
cities in China, including 42 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Kentucky's Qianmen Fried Chicken Restaurant is the earliest one
set up in China as well as the largest one in the world.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jianzhong said that the close of Kentucky's restaurant in
Beihai Park will not affect its business in Beijing and in China.
</P>
<P>
He said that Kentucky remains confident in its presence in
China and it will increase investment in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the past six months, Kentucky opened 10 new
restaurants in Beijing. "I believe Kentucky will increase the
number of the restaurants to 50 in the city by the end of this
year," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang disclosed that of Kentucky's 42 restaurants in Beijing,
the one in Beihai Park is in the middle in business volume.
</P>
<P>
Located to the northwest of the Imperial Palace, Beihai Park
was built 500 year ago and it is one of few imperial parks
maintained intact in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
