<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Ministry, Siemens Sign Memorandum for Personnel Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 26 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Personnel
and Siemens of Germany signed a memorandum of understanding here
today to enhance management and talent training for the opening up
of western China.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum marks a new stage in China's cooperation with
world-known enterprises for business personnel training.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Personnel and Siemens began their collaboration
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, the ministry has selected more than 50
leaders of large state-owned enterprises to go to Germany and
study modern enterprise management and transnational business
strategy.
</P>
<P>
The State Administrative College also cooperated with Siemens
in 1996, and it has sent 180 entrepreneurs to Germany for training
and research.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xuezhong, vice-minister of personnel, said that at
present, the ministry is focusing on the development of western
China to promote talent resources, adding that it will be of value
for China to learn from Siemens' experience. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
