<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan Uncovers Illegal Wildlife Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 26 (Xinhua) -- China's Honghe Border police
uncovered two cases involving illegal sales of 126 cobras and 25
turtles yesterday and today in the southern part of southwest
China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The cobra has been listed among the first-class of wild animals
under national protection, and the cobras and turtles will be
returned to the wild, said police officials.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan shares its southern border with Vietnam and Laos.
</P>
</TEXT>
