<HEADLINE> Over 160 Rwandan Refugees Return Home From Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- More than 160 Rwandan refugees
have voluntarily returned from the Democratic Republic of the
Congo (DRC), Rwanda News Agency reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The repatriation exercise has been going on for the last six
months but the number was small compared to the one repatriated
today," said Jean Baptiste Muhirwa, prefect of Gisenyi prefecture.
</P>
<P>
"The refugees are being camped at Nkamira where relief services
are given to them, they will later be taken to their communes of
origin," he said.
</P>
<P>
The refugees have voluntarily returned to Rwanda in response to
 President Paul Kagame's call to return and join in nation
building.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda has so far repatriated over 3 million refugees since the
end of the civil war in 1994. 
</P>
