<HEADLINE> UAE Donates Two Planes to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates
(UAE) Thursday donated two passenger planes to the Tanzania
People's Defense Forces (TPDF).
</P>
<P>
A TPDF statement said that the two planes, Antonov 28 with a
capacity of carrying 17 passengers, two pilots and a one-ton
cargo, were handed over to Tanzanian Defense Minister Edgar
Maokola-Majogo in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
Majogo said at a brief ceremony held at Ukonga air base that
the two planes would greatly help in distribution of drugs and
other national commitments of immediate urgency.
</P>
<P>
He commended the UAE for its donation, saying that "the
Tanzanian army has a myriad of aviation issues to handle but is
handicapped by shortage of planes."
</P>
<P>
UAE representative Colonel Hussein Al Moalla said that his
country would also look into possibilities of providing spare
parts for the planes.
</P>
<P>
The statement did not mention the total value of the planes. It
is reported that Tanzania has an air force of some 4,000-men with
a small amount of military planes including fighters and
transportation planes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
