<HEADLINE> Elian's Classmates To Go to United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The group is made up of four Elian's classmates, two girls and
two boys, and three mothers, a father and a pediatrician, who
accompany the minors.
</P>
<P>
Castro said in a brief chat with the press that he is confident
that the children's trip will contribute to Elian's rehabilitation,
who together with his father, his step mother, and baby brother
remains in the Wye Plantation residence, in Washington's outskirts.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban boy joined his cousin Yasmany Betancourt and his
kindergarten teacher Agueda Fleitas in Wye Plantation, who
traveled Wednesday from Havana, via Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Elian Gonzaloes survived in November a wreckage of immigrants,
in which his mother and stepfather drowned, after being picked up
off the Florida coast, and was given in custody to some far-
removed relatives who live in Miami.
</P>
<P>
These relatives refused to hand the boy over to his father Juan
Miguel Gonzalez, who lives in the island, and after a five-month
controversy, he was pulled out of the house in Miami in a U.S.
Immigration and Naturalization Service flash operation.
</P>
<P>
The boy joined then his father, who had traveled to Washington,
and now they must await for the decision of an Atlanta Court of
Appeals, which will decide May 11 on a request of political asylum
for Elian filed by the Miami relatives.
</P>
<P>
The retention of Elian in the United States, considered a
kidnapping by the Cuban authorities, created a wave of
demonstrations in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban authorities considered sending a group of children,
Elian's classmates, for the psychological recovery of the minor.
</P>
