<HEADLINE> Zambia Implements Environmental Support Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's implementation of the
Environmental Support Program (ESP) would stimulate interest and
investment in environmental and natural resources management
within a framework of economic growth, a senior government
official has said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the official opening of the Dissemination workshop
under the auspices of the Pilot Environmental Fund (PEF) here on
Thursday, Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Environment and
Natural Resources Jewitte Masinja said the major focus of PEF is
to support community-based programs.
</P>
<P>
PEF has two components, namely the Community-Based Investment
Fund (CBIF) and the Environmental Study Fund (ESF), he said.
</P>
<P>
He explained that CBIF and ESF encouraged community ownership
and management of the environment through the promotion of
community-based micro-projects.
</P>
<P>
Masinja also noted that financing practically oriented natural
resources management and environmental studies is especially of
national importance to CBIF and ESF.
</P>
<P>
"The ESF is financed by a credit to the government from the
World Bank and this credit is administered by the International
Development Agency through the environmental support program in my
ministry in conjunction with the Social Recovery Project," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He observed that all the studies financed were practical and
geared to problem solving and relevant to policy issues rather
than being solely of academic interest. 
</P>
