<HEADLINE> Shanghai Completes New Public Health System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- With the last establishment
today of a disease prevention center and a public health
institutions supervision bureau in the Pudong New Area, Shanghai
now has a citywide disease prevention system.
</P>
<P>
Two components of the new system will be responsible for
closely monitoring and carrying out laws related to prevention
efforts, and this is expected to strengthen public health
institutions in their epidemic prevention and research and studies,
said officials with the local public health bureau.
</P>
<P>
Emerging new diseases such as AIDS requires a public health
system for stern controls, and the new structure will also
intensify work in the area of non-infectious illnesses studies and
prevention, according to officials.
</P>
<P>
The old system, made up only of epidemic prevention stations,
did, however, play a positive role in public health since its
establishment along with the founding of new China in 1949, and
life expectancy in Shanghai is now 77.3 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
