<HEADLINE> Angola Government Destroys Captured Rebel Munition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Angolan government announced here
on Thursday that its concerned department had destroyed in this
month in the southeast Cuando Cubango Province some 30 tons of
munitions seized by the government troops from the rebels led by
Jonas Savimbi.
</P>
<P>
According to a spokesman for the department for landmine
removal and destruction of munitions, those explosives and
munitions destroyed near the provincial capital Menongue included
two ground-to-air missiles, 144 anti- tank mines and 202
anti-personnel mines, among other war materiel.
</P>
<P>
The weapons and munitions were seized in the region from the
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA)
through army operations, said the spokesman, adding that the
mine-clearance operations in Cuando Cubango, which has suspended
for three years, are expected to begin again in near future.
</P>
</TEXT>
