<HEADLINE> Belarussian Parliament Ratifies Nuclear Test Ban Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Belarussian National Assembly
(the parliament) ratified the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT)
on Thursday, six days after Russia made the same move, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
By ratifying the pact, Belarus has confirmed its support for
steps to eliminate nuclear weapons and Belarussian President
Alexander Lukashenko's plan to set up a nuclear-free zone in
Europe, said the Belarus Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Under the CTBT treaty which was signed by Belarus in 1996, the
country will not conduct any nuclear blasts. Belarus is the 55th
country to sign the treaty.
</P>
<P>
The United States, with the largest and most advanced nuclear
arsenal in the world, has not approved the CTBT yet. The U.S.
Senate rejected it in late 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
