<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Economic Exchange Meeting Opens in Wuhan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN,April 27 (Xinhua) -- The 20th annual session of Sino-
Japanese Economic Knowledge Exchange Meeting opened today in Wuhan,
capital of central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
In her letter of congratulations to the opening of the meeting,
State Councilor Wu Yi said that past meetings have had a positive
impact on economic and technological cooperation and economic
knowledge exchanges between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that facing the 21st century, China needs to learn from
international experiences in economic development and to study
economics.
</P>
<P>
She said that in the coming century it will be beneficial for
China and Japan to continue these exchanges and further enhance
dialogue between the scholars and economists of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yi is an advisor to the Sino-Japanese Economic Knowledge
Exchange Meeting. The Chinese and Japanese delegations consist of
economists and scholars and entrepreneurs and government officials.
</P>
</TEXT>
