<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province Attracts Talent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Five scientists were provided with
a total of 2.3 million yuan today as subsidies to carry out
scientific research and relocate in northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
They include a member of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS),
a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering (CAE), and three
professors back home from abroad.
</P>
<P>
This is part of the province's efforts to introduce talents in
order to boost its economy. China is now in the midst of a
national campaign to develop its western region, which includes
Shaanxi.
</P>
<P>
In line with regulations, a CAS or CAE member will receive 700,
000 yuan in subsidies when he or she becomes a faculty member at
an institution of higher learning in the province.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities said they will provide good living conditions
and preferential policies for talented people who relocate in
Shaanxi.  
</P>
</TEXT>
