<HEADLINE> Nokia and NEU-Alpine Provide Wireless Data Solution in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- One of China's largest software
suppliers, Shenyang Neu-Alpine software co. Ltd and Finland-based
Nokia have signed an agreement today to establish a joint venture
to develop wireless data solutions and services for Chinese
telecom operators.
</P>
<P>
The wireless application products and solutions to be provided
will comprise of hardware, software, content, training, systems
integration and maintenance services. These services and solutions
will be specifically developed for the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
As a fast growing and emerging market for the telecom and
Internet industries, China is a front-runner in rapidly moving
towards the mobile information society. China's largest telecom
operator, China Mobile, launched WAP services in six major cities
on March 28. China Unicom also launched the services in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
As the first Chinese software company to become publicly listed,
the Neu-Alpine software Co. Ltd has been providing billing systems,
client service management and call center application systems to
GSM operators. In 1999, the company completed sales volume of 730
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Nokia is the leading mobile phone supplier in the world and in
1999, its net sales totaled 19.9 billion US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
