<HEADLINE> Chinese, ROK Foreign Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan and Republic of Korea (ROK) Foreign and Trade Minister Lee
Joung-Binn reached extensive consensus during their talks today.
</P>
<P>
Both sides expressed their satisfaction with the development of
bilateral relations during the past years.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral relations have achieved rapid and comprehensive
development since the establishment of diplomatic ties, thanks to
the efforts of both sides, said Tang, noting that the fields for
cooperation have been expanded, and trade and economic cooperation
has scored unprecedented development.
</P>
<P>
Tang pointed out that the establishment of the strategy to
develop China's west has created broad prospects for bilateral
cooperation. China attaches importance to its relations with the
ROK and hopes to push ties forward, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
Lee Joung-Binn agreed that bilateral relations have seen rapid
and concrete development in political and economic aspects since
the countries established diplomatic ties eight years ago. He
noted that frequent exchanges of high-level visit have accelerated
the development of relations.
</P>
<P>
Lee expressed satisfaction that many cooperative projects have
been fruitful and are processing smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Tang also stated China's principled stand on the Taiwan issue.
Lee said the ROK has always adhered to the "one China" policy,
which has not changed, and will continue its adherence to the
guidelines set in the joint communique when the two countries
established diplomatic ties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
