<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Estimates Pakistan GDP at 4.5 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
expects the GDP growth in Pakistan at 4.5 percent during 1999-2000
and 5 percent for the next year, according to its annual report --
the Asian Development 2000 Outlook.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that the country's industrial growth may
remain stagnant, but the agriculture sector could improve because
of more investment. However, the report says the medium-term
outlook depended critically on the political stability and the
pace of economic reforms in the country.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the economic performance in the first half of the
1999-2000 fiscal year showed a slow but fragile recovery. While
the industrial growth remained sluggish because of low investment,
improvement in the agriculture sector partially offset the loss.
</P>
</TEXT>
