<HEADLINE> Share Prices Maintain Upturn Trend on S'pore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices maintained the
upturn trend on Singapore Stock Market Thursday following
Wednesday's two percent upsurge.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) surged up 42.92 points
to close at 2,151.72 points with intraday high hitting the level
of 2,161.68 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume increased to 297.14 million shares valued at
608.61 million Singapore dollars (about 356.68  million U.S.
dollars). Gainers outstripped losers by 243 to 85 with 202
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
ParkwayLab topped the volume list as it registered a turnover
of 22.83 million units. FoodEmpire was the second most heavily-
traded stock with 21.09 million shares done. MHE was the next with
13.18 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture was the biggest gainer of the day jumping up 210 cents
to close at 19.30 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 ran up 140 cents to
finish at 33.80 Singapore dollars. Datacrft was the next picking
up 125 cents to end at 7.80 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led losers of the day sinking by 70 cents to close
at 37.00 Singapore dollars. StarCru trimmed 45 cents to finish at
7.50 U.S. dollars. F&AMP;N retreated 20 cents to end at 5.60 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that selective technology stocks edged up despite
the U.S. market's overall weakness on fears of higher interest
rates.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said that as the U.S. is waiting for some key economic
numbers to come out, caution prevailed over the market and
investors were just making short-term trades.  
</P>
</TEXT>
