<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Anti-drug NGOs Meet in Bangkok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of anti-drug
nongovernmental organizations from the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) met here Thursday at a workshop, striving to
find an effective drug abuse preventive strategy.
</P>
<P>
About 150 representatives from eight of 10 ASEAN member
countries participated in the 10th International Federation of
Nongovernmental Organization for the Prevention of Drug and
Substance Abuse (IFNGO) ASEAN NGOs Workshop. Cambodia and Laos did
not send representatives to participate in this workshop.
</P>
<P>
The workshop also aims to strengthen coordination and
communication among ASEAN NGOs on drug abuse prevention, formulate
the effective program to prevent drug abuse in the family group
and among the youth and evaluate the implementation of prevention
programs of ASEAN NGOs.
</P>
<P>
The host of the workshop is NGO-Anti Narcotics Coordinating
Center of the National Council of the International Council on
Social Welfare of Thailand, which is a founding member of IFNGO.
</P>
<P>
The workshop will feature topics on drug legislation, youth
participation, alternative/positive internet access training, GO
and NGO cooperation and collaboration for ASEAN solidarity against
drug and substance abuse, role of religion on drug abuse
prevention, primary effective program for youth and effective
media program.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that plans of action of each ASEAN NGO and ASEAN-
NGO project to enhance intra-ASEAN cooperation and coordination in
drug abuse prevention will be finished before the closing of the
workshop on Saturday. 
</P>
