in downtown Harare.
</P>
<P>
Tension is mounting in the run up to the country's fifth
parliamentary elections next month with the ruling Zanu-pf party
facing the biggest challenge from the opposition Movement for
Democratic Change since independence in 1980.
</P>
<P>
Observers said political violence had made negative impact on
the country's tourism sector.
</P>
<P>
Hotels in Zimbabwe's premier resort Victoria Falls were
experiencing one of the lowest occupancy rates since 1980.
