based in Shanghai, Hong Kong and Taiwan gathered here today at a
seminar on banking cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The three banking institutions are the local Bank of Shanghai,
and the Shanghai Commercial Bank and Shanghai Commercial and
Savings Bank based in Hong Kong and Taiwan respectively.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the People's Bank of China and Shanghai
municipal government, and senior directors of the three banks
attended the seminar and discussed prospects of joint development
and long-term cooperation to face the challenges and opportunities
after China enters the World Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
The three banks will cooperate in a variety of banking services
such as asset restructuring, equity transfer, payment and credit,
among others, to attract more clients.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the banks will host regular information
exchanges in economic, finance and law fields.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan-based Shanghai Commercial and Savings Bank was set
up in Shanghai in 1915, the Hong Kong business is an entity
separated from the Taiwan bank, and the Shanghai bank was
established in 1995. Two years ago, they hosted a similar seminar.
</P>
