<HEADLINE> China And Japan Build Flood Monitoring System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A flood and environmental
monitoring system was recently launched by the Chinese Academy of
Sciences (CAS) with the help of the Japanese Hitachi Ltd. in order
to prevent and control flood disasters in China.
</P>
<P>
The Hitachi Ltd. provided the Institute of Remote Sensing
Application under CAS with advanced monitoring facilities and
computer software worth 1.5 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to a report in "Science Times", the devastating
floods along the Yangtze River in 1998 drew a huge reaction from
scientific and industrial sectors in both China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
In November 1998 when Chinese President Jiang Zemin visited
Japan, 33 flood control, agricultural, environmental and
information projects were signed. The environmental and flood
monitoring system was included in these projects.
</P>
<P>
The system will help forecast natural disasters, relieve flood
disasters and offer information on the environment. 
</P>
