<HEADLINE> Chinese Procuratorate to Target Misuse of Administrative Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Supreme People's
Procuratorate (SPP) said today that people's procuratorates at
various levels will focus their investigation and prosecution on
four categories of cases with the misuse of administrative power.
</P>
<P>
The first category involves dereliction of duty and abuse of
power by officials above the county level.
</P>
<P>
Cases involving the practice of favoritism, perverting the law,
extorting confessions by torture and unlawful detention by
judicial functionary fall into the second category.
</P>
<P>
The third category of cases include the misuse of
administrative power and irregularities of by law enforcement
authorities, especially those who responsible for economic order
and security.
</P>
<P>
The violation of legal and democratic rights and interests of
citizens, especially illegal custody of delegates to the people's
congress, is the fourth category.
</P>
<P>
The SPP will also focus on cases are harmful to reforms in
state-owned enterprises and the development of China's western
regions. These cases include the misuse of administrative power to
interfere with the reform in state-owned enterprises and other
illegal activities which harm the interests of the state and the
people.
</P>
<P>
The crackdown on these cases will help build a diligent and
clean government and promote the development of a market economy
with socialist characteristics, the SPP said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
