<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks End Slightly Lower in Thin Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed
slightly lower Thursday with the lowest trade volume in five
months, ahead of the release of U.S. economic data.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index shed 34.52 points, or 0.23 percent, to
close at 15,192.87. The turnover was only 6.969 billion HK dollars
(893 million U.S. dollars), as against the previous trading volume
of 8.026 billion HK dollars (1.057 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Brokers said many investors preferred to stand on the sidelines
ahead of the release of U.S. gross domestic product data and the
employment cost index later on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices, Utilities and Properties gained 0.93
percent and 0.74 percent, while Finance and Commerce and Industry
lost 0.81 percent and 0.31 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index went down 2.43 percent and 0.31 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
IT-related index ended mixed with the Hang Seng IT Index down 1.
04 percent and the Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index up 0.97 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong stocks slid slightly 2.22 points, or 0.01 percent,
to open at 15,225.17 Thursday morning. The blue chips were down 91.
95 points, or 0.60 percent, to close the morning session at 15.135.
44. 
</P>
</TEXT>
