<HEADLINE> Nokia to Deliver First Commercial WAP Solution in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Nokia signed its first contract
with the Jilin Mobile Communication Company (Jilin MCC) yesterday
offering a commercial wireless application protocol (WAP) solution.
</P>
<P>
Nokia have begun to provide Jilin MCC, based in northeast
China's Jilin province, the Nokia Artus Messaging Platform,
including both WAP gateway and message modules, according to
Malcolm Arnold, vice president of the system business department
under Nokia(China) Investment Co..
</P>
<P>
Jilin MCC can offer mobile internet services to all GSM users
who have phones that support short messages, even if they don't
have WAP-enabled phones.
</P>
<P>
Jilin MCC has one million subscribers and operates GSM 900 and
GSM 1800 networks in Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
"Nokia is pleased to work with Jilin MCC as the first operator
in China to take Nokia's commercial WAP solution, which will
further strength our commitment to working with Chinese Business,"
Arnold said. 
