<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Starts Personnel Reform in National Health Care System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- China will launch health care
reforms to cut off redundant staff and encourage competition,
according to a meeting of personnel held by the Ministry of Health
in Beijing on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Health has decided to spend three to five
years to form a new personnel system under which medical
organizations at all levels have the rights to select their
employees while medical staff can choose positions according to
their ability.
</P>
<P>
The new system will provide a more flexibility in management,
payment and promotion. Everybody will be judged according to their
performance, and no position will be permanent.
</P>
<P>
After the reforms are implemented, the number of people with
professional skills will make up 80 percent of the total number of
staff in the medical system. Work of officials at the grass-roots
levels will be appraised by their subordinates.
</P>
<P>
The distribution system will also be reformed to guarantee that
those who have higher professional skills provide better medical
service, take on more responsibilities, and are paid more.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
