<HEADLINE> Monitoring System To Quarantine Fruit Flies from Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- China is developing a monitoring
system to quarantine fruit flies from abroad, officials said.
</P>
<P>
The State Administration for Entry-Exit Inspection and
Quarantine has issued a circular asking its local branches to step
up development of the system to prevent the spreading of fruit
flies.
</P>
<P>
Apart from guarding against the import of fruit flies, the
monitoring system is also conducive to the promotion of Chinese
fruits abroad, the administration said.
</P>
<P>
The monitoring system consists of a network covering fruit-
importing ports, tourist resorts and fruit-producing areas
nationwide. A total of twenty-seven quarantine bureaus in major
cities including Guangzhou and Shenzhen will be involved in
setting up the monitoring system.  
</P>
