<HEADLINE> 8 Injured in Explosion in Southeast Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Eight workers Thursday were
injured in an explosion and fire at a substation at Orange in the
central west of the New South Wales state in southeast Australia,
emergency services said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred at the Lords Place substation soon after
2 p.m. (local time), a fire brigade spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report of the cause of the explosion.
</P>
<P>
Two of the eight workers sustained burns in the explosion and
the other six were treated for smoke inhalation, an ambulance
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Fire fighters used carbon dioxide gas to fight the blaze.
</P>
<P>
A brigade spokesman said parts of Orange would be without power
for several hours. 
</P>
