<HEADLINE> Model Workers Arrive in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The first group of Chinese model
workers to be commended in the running up to the International
Labor Day on May 1 arrived in Beijing early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The 130 model workers are from central China's province of
Henan. They were followed by 90 model workers from north China's
Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the reception office of the organizing committee
of the model workers gathering said that all the model workers
will arrive in Beijing by this evening.
</P>
<P>
The State Council will hold a large-scale meeting here on April
29, at which 2,950 model workers will be cited for their
contributions to the reform and opening-up and socialist
modernization drive over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Of all the model workers, those from enterprises account for 36.
78 percent and peasants for 19 percent, while scientists,
engineers and technicians and teachers make up 27.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The model workers are also scheduled to tour the Great Wall and
the Tiananmen Square. They will begin to leave for home on April
30. 
</P>
