<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Some 400 Angolan refugees are
entering Zambia every week following the escalation of the civil
war in their country, according to United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
UNHCR public information assistant Kelvin Shimoon told Times of
Zambia newspaper Wednesday that the number of new arrivals at
Maheba and Mayukwakwa in North-Western Province had shot up to
6,000.
</P>
<P>
