<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices moved lower in Tokyo
Thursday as investors were reluctant to buy stocks due to
uncertainty over the course on Wall Street, with the key Nikkei
index falling to a closing low for the year.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 115.14 points, or 0.63
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at 18,019.17.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, dropped 23.67 points, or 1.42 percent, to 1,
644.22.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 542.31 million
shares from Wednesday's 551.87 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Investors stayed on the sidelines ahead of the release later
Thursday of U.S. gross domestic product figures and the U.S.
employment cost index, both for the first quarter of this year,
traders said.
</P>
<P>
They were also hesitant to actively buy stocks ahead of Japan's
Golden Week holiday period, which starts this weekend and ends May
7, they said.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Paper manufacturers, rubber makers and real estate firms saw
large declines, while oil distributors, nonferrous metal makers
and wholesalers gained ground.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers far exceeded
gainers 955 to 307, while 122 issues closed unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
