<HEADLINE> Suspect of Bomb Blast in Harare Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 27 (Xinhua) -- South African journalist Obert
Siyabuliza Zilwa was arrested Wednesday at Harare International
Airport on suspicion of involvement in the Easter bomb blast in
downtown Harare.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwe Broadcasting Corporation reported that Zilwa, who
works for an international news organization, entered the country
on April 5 this year. He hired a vehicle, which police believed
was used in the attack on the art gallery under the offices of The
Daily News.
</P>
<P>
A police official said Zilwa was expected to appear in court on
Friday adding police investigations are continuing.
</P>
<P>
