<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cholera Outbreak Kills 9 in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Nine people have died of cholera
in a town of west Kenya in the past two weeks, the Daily Nation
newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Six others were admitted to hospital in serious conditions at
Luanda Division, Vihiga District in Western Province, according to
District Officer Willis Cheboi.
</P>
<P>
Cheboi said that the council would protect all the sources of
water in he town while blaming the outbreak of cholera on poor
hygiene.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan government sounded a cholera alert in Nyanza and
Western Provinces in early April after 24 people died in March.
</P>
<P>
Cholera, a water-borne disease, claimed at least 1,000 lives in
one of its worst outbreaks in Nyanza Province in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
