<HEADLINE> Third Preparatory Meeting for Inter-Korean Summit to Open Next Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Seoul and Pyongyang Thursday agreed
to hold their third preparatory meeting at the truce village of
Panmunjom next Wednesday for the inter-Korean summit on June 12-14.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached at the second preparatory meeting
held at Tongilgak (Unification House), north of Panmunjom.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's chief delegate Yang Young-shil told a press
conference that the second meeting is "productive and pragmatic"
and the two sides are narrowing their gaps on many issues.
</P>
<P>
