meeting has focused on procedural matters and numbers of delegates
from the two sides to participate in the summit.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean top delegate said that the third preparatory
meeting will focus on the summit procedure.
</P>
<P>
As a breakthrough after half-century confrontation, Seoul and
Pyongyang reached an agreement in China on April 8, under which,
South Korean President Kim Dae-jung will travel to Pyongyang to
meet with Kim Jong Il, leader of the Democratic People's Republic
of Korea. 
