<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE -- The Czech koruna, the country's currency, dived on
Wednesday to its lowest point against the U.S. dollar since it
became an exchangeable currency in 1995, thus triggering concerns
in the country's economic circles.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate between the dollar and koruna was 1:39.4,
approaching once again the psychological tolerance level of 1:40.
The exchange rate between the two currencies has repeatedly
approached this point in the recent week, mainly due to the recent
weakness in the euro. (Czech-Dollar)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HARARE -- Zimbabwe's 2000 tobacco marketing season started at
low note here on Wednesday amid calls for an improved exchange
rate and fears that commercial farmers would withhold their crop
due to farm invasions by war veterans.
</P>
<P>
Managing Director of the Tobacco Sales Floor Pat Devenish said
that the slow start was largely due to the incorrect exchange rate
and farm invasions which had resulted in some farmers being chased
away and their workers beaten up. (Zimbabwe-Tobacco)
</P>
