BRUSSELS -- The European Union remained silent on Wednesday
though the euro fell to record low against the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
Jonathan Faull, spokesman of EU's executive European Commission,
told the day's routine press briefing that he had no comment to
make though he had been asked to comment on the record fall of the
single currency. (EU-Euro) 
