<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CIH Virus Hits Computers in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of computers across the
country came under attack of CIH virus on Wednesday, the New
Nation newspaper reported here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The virus, Known as "Chernobyl Computer Virus," is presumed to
hit every year on April 26, the day of Chernobyl disaster.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Bangladesh Computer Council told the
newspaper that the disaster this year mainly occurred on
individual personal computers, causing less damage than last year.
The number of the affected computers are around 500.
</P>
<P>
CIH works under Windows 95 and Windows 98. There is no report
of attack on Windows 2000 and Windows NT yet. Two problems CIH can
create are data loss of the hard disc and damage to flash BOIS
which prevents the computers from booting.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh computer vendors' association advised the affected
computer users to collect Tiramish software which is best for data
recovery in experts' opinion free of cost from their respective
vendors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
