<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats Ecuador 3-2 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazil came from behind to edge
Ecuador 3-2 in a World Cup qualifier in Sao Paulo on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador stunned the four-times world champions by taking an
early lead with a magnificent goal by Alex Aguinaga in the 12th
minute.
</P>
<P>
Brazil turned the game around with two close range goals by
Rivaldo and one by defender Antonio Carlos.
</P>
<P>
The result left Brazil with four points from two games in the
South American qualifying group, one more than Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador, who have never beaten Brazil, never qualified for the
World Cup and lost the last meeting between the teams 5-1.
</P>
<P>
After Ecuador scored the opening goal, the fickle Sao Paulo
crowd quickly began to jeer their team until Rivaldo equalised
five minutes later with a shot on the turn from close range.
</P>
<P>
Brazil went ahead two minutes before halftime, when Antonio
Carlos, who had stayed up after a corner, scored from close range.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilians then appeared to be cruising when Rivaldo netted
again in the 52nd minute.
</P>
<P>
But Ecuador refused to capitulate and 14 minutes from time when
de la Cruz scored with a dipping left foot shot into the top
corner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
