<HEADLINE> Thai Trade Surplus Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Thailand gained a trade surplus
of 3.24 billion U.S. dollars in the first quarter of this year, an
increase of over 30 percent over the previous year, Thai Finance
Ministry announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Thai Finance Ministry Spokesman Sathit Limpongpan said in a
news conference that in the first quarter of this year, trade
surplus increased 1.70 billion dollars over the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Thai exports to overseas markets accounted for 17.07 billion
dollars, while imports in the first quarter were 13.83 billion
dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
Major Thai exports in the first quarter included computers and
accessories, electrical appliances, and plastic products; while
major imports were electric machines, chemical products and other
machinery, he stated. 
</P>
