<HEADLINE> IUOL Expecting to Launch IP Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- International United On-Line Co.
Ltd. (IUOL), one of China's first Internet service providers, is
expecting to become the country's fifth IP operator if it gets IP
operation permit from the Chinese Ministry of Information Industry
(MII).
</P>
<P>
By now, only four network firms of China Telecom, China Unicom,
JiTong Communication and China Netcom are allowed to operate IP
service in the country.
</P>
<P>
MII has issued a public notice to open up China's IP market,
and published a range of regulations to standardize IP operation,
including "General Technical Requirement for IP and Facsimile
Service", "Interconnection Technical Specification for IP Gateway
Equipment". It promised to select more qualified network companies
to run IP service.
</P>
<P>
IUOL, the Beijing-based network firm, has just forged a
strategic alliance with a number of large IP technical and
equipment providers. It will use the VoIP value-added service,
PoP fiber network and NAP global communication platform developed
by the iBasis to promote China's IP service.
</P>
<P>
Fan Wei, Chairman of IUOL, said that if his company is given
the license, they will concentrate on establishing a VoIP network
connecting the mainland with overseas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
