<HEADLINE> Experts Call for Eating Less Fat, Doing More Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Overweight people had better take
steps to get rid of flab so as to avoid suffering from
hypertension, diabetes and other diseases.
</P>
<P>
The warning was made by the health experts who attended an
international workshop on obesity that concluded yesterday, China
Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
With the improvement of living standard, an increasing number
of people in China eat more fatty foods, and obesity has become a
national health problem, said Kong Lingzhi of the Department for
Disease Control, a branch of the Ministry of Health.
</P>
<P>
Kong attributes obesity to eating too much fat and a lack of
exercise.
</P>
<P>
In China, 100 million people suffer from hypertension, while 26
million have diabetes. Obesity is a factor that can not be ignored,
Kong said.
</P>
<P>
Chen Chunming, a nutrition professor said obesity is caused by
hereditary factors and a high intake of fat.
</P>
<P>
Chen also warned that the practice of taking diet pills without
the supervision of a doctor can be harmful.
</P>
<P>
The workshop, sponsored by the International Life Sciences
Institute Focal Point on China, attracted researchers from China,
the United States, Britain, Germany, and Australia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
