information technology industry and "new economy," the ADB said it
was crucial for Hong Kong to stay attractive for highly skilled
workers from the mainland and elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
To achieve this target, the bank underlined the importance of
addressing Hong Kong's worsening pollution, which it said was
causing increasing concern over health.
</P>
