<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mercosur Satisfied with Russian Approval of START II </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Southern
Common Market (Mercosur) Wednesday expressed their satisfaction
over the ratification of the second-phase Strategic Arms Reduction
Treaty (START II) in the Russian Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Russian State Duma or Parliament ratified the treaty on
April 14, under which the United States and Russia agree to reduce
the number of nuclear warheads from 6,000 to no more than 3,500 by
2007.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, composed by Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay,
with Bolivia and Chile as associate members, released a
declaration on START II during its Political Consultation and
Coordination Forum here.
</P>
<P>
According to the declaration, the six countries see the
achievement of START II as contribution to the strengthening of
world strategic security, and giving renewed strength to the world
trend toward future reduction and eventual elimination of nuclear
weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
