<HEADLINE> Croatia Beats Austria 2-1 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Croatia beat the host Austria 2-1
in an international soccer friendly here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The technically superior and much faster Croats, who are ranked
tenth in the world, dominated throughout the game, although in the
second half they began to be defensive.
</P>
<P>
Austria's first and only goal in the 17th minute came suddenly
when Andreas Herzog served Ivica Vastic of Sturm Graz with a long
pass, and the Croat-born mainstay in the Austrian team scored from
sixteen meters.
</P>
<P>
In the 24th minute, Aljosa Asanovic failed to convert a penalty.
But star forward Alen Boksic made it 1-1 in the 28th minute when
Thomas Floegel deflected his shot into the net.
</P>
<P>
The well-organized Croats, who beat the Austrians many times,
again increased their pressure in the second half, and Mario
Stanic made it 2-1 from a melee in front of the Austrian goal.
