<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, April 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA -- A delegation of U.S. farmers from Texas Wednesday
called for a gradual lessening of the blockade imposed by
Washington upon Cuba four decades ago.
</P>
<P>
The president of the Grains Federation of Texas, Donald Patman,
read a declaration during a press conference here in which he said
that "the embargo against Cuba has failed in a spectacular way"
and that "the use of food as a weapon is a low despicable issue."
</P>
<P>
The document said that Texan farmers' families are convinced
that it is better to use the abundant agricultural produce as a
peace and cooperation tool among nations.
</P>
<P>
The 19-member delegation, which arrived here Monday and
finished its visit Wednesday, was accompanied during its visit to
the island by U.S. Democrat congressman from Texas Charles
Stemholm, also a member of the Congress Agricultural Committee. (
Cuba-US-Blockade)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The United Nations is seeking some 9.5 million
U.S. dollars in aid for the victims of the explosion of the
Chernobyl nuclear reactor 14 years ago, U.N. spokesperson Marie
Okabe said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The projects "are minimum the international community should do,
" she quoted U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan as saying in a new
publication "Chernobyl: A Continuing Catastrophe."
</P>
<P>
Seven million people in Ukraine, Belarus and Russia are still
suffering the effects of the incident, according to the U.N.
Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs. Among them,
three million children require physical treatment. (UN-Chernobyl
Victims)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India and Russia will hold talks on security-
related issues during the visit of Russian Secretary of National
Security Council Sergei Ivanov, who is due to arrive here later
Wednesday evening, sources with the Indian External Affairs
Ministry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov, who is heading a high-level Russian delegation, will
hold talks with his counterpart Indian National Security Advisor
Brajesh Mishra and also sign a protocol with the Indian side, the
sources added.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day stay, Ivanov will also call on Indian
Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee, External Affairs Minister
Jaswant Singh and Defense Minister George Fernandes, they said. (
India-Russia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Expressing its deep concern over the plight
of Kuwaitis missing since Iraq's invasion of Kuwait in 1990, the
United Nations Security Council Wednesday urged Iraq to cooperate
with the U.N. and resume cooperation with all other agencies and
bodies in dealing with this issue.
</P>
<P>
The move came after the Security Council was briefed this
morning on the issue by the U.N. Coordinator for Missing Kuwaitis
and Kuwaiti property, Yuli Vorontsov.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the press, the Council expressed its support
for the Coordinator's future efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Council expressed its hope that this issue would be dealt
with as a strictly humanitarian one by all sides concerned and
highlighted the valuable work of the International Committee of
the Red Cross. (UN-Iraq-Kuwait) 
</P>
