<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet to Invest 22 Billion Yuan in Ecological Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Region has
decided to invest 22.7 billion yuan (about 2.73 billion U.S.
dollars) in protecting the ecological environment over the next
five decades.
</P>
<P>
An official of the regional government said that the largest
environment construction program consists of 160 projects which
will be conducted in three phases.
</P>
<P>
Twelve projects are planned this year, including ecological
protection and construction at the upper reaches of the Yangtze
River and the middle reaches of the Yarlung Zangbo River.
</P>
<P>
The two projects in Jomada, Conjo, and Markam counties will
cost about 8.64 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Tibet, encompassing the major portion of the Qinghai-Tibet
Plateau, is one source of the climate in China and the world, as
well as the site of river resources and ecological resources for
China and South Asia, and the improvement of the ecological
environment of the Qinghai Tibet Plateau will benefit the
environment of the entire world.
</P>
<P>
The ecological environment program in Tibet will focus on the
creation of grasslands, forests, the protection of wildlife
resources, the returning of farmland to grassland and forests, as
well as the control of soil erosion and the elimination of
desertification.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
