<HEADLINE> New Date Set for Tyson Bout  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- American boxer Mike Tyson's next
fight, against Lou Savarese, will now take place on June 24 - more
than a month later than originally scheduled.
</P>
<P>
No official reason was given for the May 20 postponement, but
Tyson reportedly needed more time to prepare.
</P>
<P>
The former world heavyweight champion last fought on January 29,
when he stopped Julius Francis in two rounds in Manchester.
</P>
<P>
A site for the bout with Savarese is still to be determined,
according to Tyson's spokesman Peter Seligman.
</P>
<P>
The fight could still be held in Milan, but a switch to Glasgow
's Hampden Park is also reportedly being considered. 
</P>
