<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Magic's Doc Rivers Named NBA Coach of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Doc Rivers of the Orlando
Magic, who began the season with no experience and no stars and
got his team within a win of the postseason, was named NBA Coach
of the Year on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Rivers received 60 votes from the 121-member media panel, seven
more than Phil Jackson of the Los Angeles Lakers, to become the
fifth rookie coach to win the award. Paul Silas of the Charlotte
Hornets was a distant third with three votes.
</P>
<P>
The first-year coach Rivers led the Magic to a 41-41 record,
battling for an Eastern Conference playoff spot until the season's
penultimate game, when they suffered a last-second 85-83 home loss
to the Milwaukee Bucks that finally knocked them out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
