<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Defeats United States 2-0 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Yegor Titov and Valery Karpin
scored two second-half goals to give Russia a 2-0 victory over the
United States in the first soccer international match between the
two rivals here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Andrei Tikhonov found his Spartak Moscow teammate Titov with a
through ball and he went around American goalkeeper Kasey Keller
and slotted into an empty net to give Russia the lead after 53
minutes.
</P>
<P>
As the Americans pressed for the equaliser in the later stages
of the match, Alexander Panov found Karpin unmarked in front of
the American goal and the Celta Vigo midfielder scored in the
seconds.
</P>
<P>
American captain Claudio Reyno had the best chance for the
visitors when he went one-on-one with Ruslan Nigmatullin in the
25th minute, but the goalkeeper made a save from close range.
</P>
<P>
It was the 10th meeting between the two countries with Russia
now having won six matches, the United States once with three
games drawn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
