<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets S. African Top Lawmaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAPE TOWN, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin Wednesday expressed his hope that South Africa will
score new achievement in the construction of the country.
</P>
<P>
China, as a friend of South Africa, is pleased to see the
progress that South Africa has made, Jiang said during a meeting
here with Frene Ginwala, speaker of the National Assembly of South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived in Cape Town, the legislature capital of South
Africa, from Pretoria Wednesday afternoon to continue his state
visit to the country.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president cited Ginwala as an old friend of China
who has made significant contributions to the advancement of
Sino-South African relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the exchanges between China's National People's
Congress and South Africa's Parliament have constituted an
important part of the bilateral relations because both of them are
playing an important role in the political life of their
respective countries.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that Ginwala will continue to make
efforts to consolidate the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Extending his warm welcome to Jiang, Ginwala congratulated him
on his success of the tour.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is the last leg of Jiang's five-nation tour. The
visit has brought him to Israel, Palestine, Turkey and Greece.
Jiang also met with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in the
Alexandria city of Egypt. 
