<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2130 GMT, Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak intends to
transfer soon to full Palestinian control the village of Abu Dis,
as an "advance" of Israel's next troop redeployment in the West
Bank, the local daily Ha'aretz Thursday quoted a senior political
source as saying.
</P>
<P>
Barak is expected to bring the proposal to his Security Cabinet
for approval next week and such a move will allay Palestinian
suspicions that Israel intends to use delaying tactics in the talks
so as to avoid transferring significant territory to the
Palestinians, the source added. (Israel-Palestinian-Redeployment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The target date for concluding a framework
agreement on the final-status issues between Israel and the
Palestinians will likely be put off again from the end of May to
the end of June, the Israeli daily Ha'aretz reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted political sources as saying that two months
of work will be needed to complete the agreement and prepare for a
trilateral summit in Washington at which U.S. President Bill
Clinton will host Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak and Palestinian
President Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
A similar signal was sent by United States Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright, who said in Washington on Wednesday that in the
six or eight weeks ahead, "very intensive" work will be needed on
the Israeli-Palestinian track. (Israel-Framework Deal-Postponement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's conservative judiciary on Thursday closed down
two more reformist papers, Sobh-e Emruz and Mosharekat, bringing
the total number of papers and periodicals suspended to 16.
</P>
<P>
Sobh-e Emruz (This Morning) is published by Saeed Hajjarian, a
prominent reformer who was shot and seriously wounded in an
assassination attempt last month, the Islamic Republic News Agency
(IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The judiciary had ordered the closure of the daily on Monday,
but revoked the order later, citing Hajjarian's hospitalization as
the reason.
</P>
<P>
Mosharekat (Participation) is run by Mohammed Reza Khatami,
brother of pro-reform President Mohammed Khatami.(Iran-Paper
Closure)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- The Palestinian National Authority (PNA) rejects any
postponement of talks on the final status issues,said a senior
Palestinian official on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Voice of Palestine radio, Mahmoud Abbas
(also known as Abu Mazen), secretary general of the Executive
Committee of Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO), said a
lasting peace must address all final status issues.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came three days before Palestinian and Israeli
negotiators are to hold a new round of talks on the last phase
redeployment of Israeli troops in the West Bank and on the final
status issues, including the status of Jerusalem, water sharing,
refugees and Jewish settlements. (Palestine-Peace Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
