<HEADLINE> Riot at Athens' Avlona Juvenile Prison Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A riot at the Avlona juvenile
prison near the Greek capital of Athens ended Thursday, with five
people being injured and 350 million drachmas (about 980,392 U.S.
dollars) in damages to the complex.
</P>
<P>
The five-hour riot broke out late Wednesday after about 30-50
inmates, mostly Albanians and Romanians, managed to reach the
prison's neutral zone and took a warden hostage, Greece's Justice
Minister Michalis Stathopoulos said late Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 inmates were involved in the rioting, during which an
inmate was stabbed in the throat and was reported in serious
condition at a hospital.
</P>
<P>
The Athens prosecutor's office is now investigating the cause
of the riot.
</P>
<P>
There have been a number of prison riots in Greece since 1995,
and most of the riots broke out due to prisoners' dissatisfaction
over their living conditions in prison. 
</P>
</TEXT>
