<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investors to Have Equal Fiscal Regime in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian government will
soon abrogate an old emergency ordinance on granting incentives to
major investors, so that the investors will have an equal fiscal
regime, government spokesperson Gabriela Vranceanu-Firea announced
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesperson, the mentioned emergency
ordinance will be abrogated by the government at one of its next
sessions. The Mugur Isarescu Cabinet's members took the decision
to create an equal fiscal regime for all investors, regardless the
sum invested or the field of activity, she added.
</P>
<P>
In the future, the incentives for the investors which created
red tape and corruption will no longer exist. Economic policies
will exist only, Vranceanu-Firea stressed.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Isarescu explained to the members of his cabinet
that they had to choose between clear and stable stipulations and
arbitrary regime in the field of investments.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson also said that after the abrogation of the
mentioned emergency ordinance, the government would approve a
general regime for investments which stipulated the exemption of
customs duties for the import of machinery and equipment for
production and not for sale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
