<HEADLINE> AT&AMP;T Wireless Issues Largest IPO In U.S. History </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 27 (Xinhua) -- AT&AMP;T issued a tracking stock for
its wireless phone business Thursday on the New York Stock
Exchange in the largest initial public offering in U.S. history.
</P>
<P>
The stock closed at 31.31 U.S. dollars a share, a moderate rise
from the initial price of 29.50 U.S. dollars per share for IPO. AT&AMP;
T announced Wednesday night it was selling 360 million shares for
a total of 10.26 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The winning IPO will give AT&AMP;T more money to build networks and
make acquisition in the competitive wireless market.
</P>
<P>
Wireless telecommunications has been one of the hottest areas
on the stock market since November 1998. Spring PCS Group saw its
stocks rise more than eight times in price between then and last
month but its stocks fell 21 percent from its peak as the tech
market plunged in the past six weeks.
</P>
<P>
The wireless tracking stock is structured much differently than
an earlier AT&AMP;T spinoff, gear maker Lucent Technologies Inc. AT&AMP;T
can still package wireless phone service with discounted long-
distance rates and superfast Internet access.
</P>
<P>
Lucent, with its own board of directors, went public in 1996 at
6.75 dollars a share. Its stock hit a high of nearly 85 dollars a
share late last year and now trades around 62 dollars per share.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
