<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Urges People to Modernize Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
 has urged the people of his country to develop agriculture,
saying that the most important message to the people now is that
of modernization of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
"The people of Uganda must seriously take up the fight against
poverty in homesteads using the prevailing tranquil environment
and democratic governance," he was quoted as saying by a press
release from the President' s Office which was available on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks when meeting with a joint delegation from
the Kigulu South in Iganga district and Bukholi in Bugiri district
at his home in Rwakitura, Mbarara district.
</P>
<P>
The president said while entrepreneurs in urban areas can
overcome poverty by joining commerce-related activities and real
estate, the people in the rural areas can equally overcome poverty
by using modern methods to grow crops, raise livestock and breed
fish.
</P>
<P>
He advised the people in Busoga region to guard against further
 fragmentation of their land.
</P>
<P>
The delegation was headed by Vice President Specioza Wandira
Kazibwe, who is also Member of Parliament (MP) for Kigulu South,
and MP for Bukholi North Abdul Nakendo. 
</P>
