<HEADLINE> Ugandan Police Exhume More Bodies From New Mass Graves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A total of 55 bodies have been
exhumed from new mass graves belonging to the Movement for the
Restoration of the Ten Commandments of God, police spokesman John
Kimera told Xinhua Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
Among the bodies were eight boys, ten girls, 22 ladies and 15
men, Kimera said, adding that the bodies were exhumed from three
graves at a house in Mawanga zone, Kampala district.
</P>
<P>
Investigation revealed that the house, which had been taken
charge of by the police several days ago, was once rented by
Dominic Kararibaabo, one of the cult's leaders.
</P>
<P>
The cult burnt to death at least 530 followers in Kanungu in
southwestern Uganda on March 17. Since then mass graves have been
discovered on the properties of the cult leaders, bringing the
total number of the dead to more than 1,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
